   "body" : "This PR is related to #19303 and gets rid of the RecursiveMutex `cs_most_recent_block`. All of the critical sections (5 in total) only directly access the guarded elements, i.e. it is not possible that within one section another one is called, and we can use a regular Mutex:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/807169e10b4a18324356ed6ee4d69587b96a7c70/src/net_processing.cpp#L1577-L1583\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/807169e10b4a18324356ed6ee4d69587b96a7c70/src/net_processing.cpp#L1790-L1795\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/807169e10b4a18324356ed6ee4d69587b96a7c70/src/net_processing.cpp#L3083-L3086\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/807169e10b4a18324356ed6ee4d69587b96a7c70/src/net_processing.cpp#L3135-L3140\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/807169e10b4a18324356ed6ee4d69587b96a7c70/src/net_processing.cpp#L4706-L4717\r\n\r\nAlso, it is renamed to adapt to the (unwritten) naming convention to use the `_mutex` suffix rather than the `cs_` prefix.",
